race.comment: CIELAO (4) bounced back sharply last start with an impressive front-running win, making light work of Extinguish who franked the form with a quick follow-up victory. A progressive type who looks set to go on with it. ROYAL SCRIPTURE (8) was a determined winner fresh before getting too far back last time, though the winner does look above average. The booking of Toeroek is a strong push and he should be able to settle closer. Looms as the main danger. SIR RANDOLPH (3) has been hitting the line well in two runs back and should be reaching peak fitness now. The extra 100m suits and he can play a major role. SPEEDTAIL (1) had no luck last start but lengthened impressively late to grab second once clear. Drawn poorly, so expect him to be rattling home again. THE LAST DANCE (6) was good fresh but disappointed last time. Backs up quickly and can rebound. Worth keeping safe.
